DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       Fullnm is a utility function that filename expands a string.  This
       includes generating the pwd (1) prefix for unqualified names as well as
       metacharacters a la csh (1).  Up to the first 'maxlen' characters of
       the output will replace the input and a count of any remaining charac-
       ters will be returned. It also attempts to strip autoumounter paths
       from the directory name.

